  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle</p><p>Add your <strong>farfalle</strong> to a pot of <strong>boiled water </strong>with a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Cook for 8-10 min or until cooked with a slight bite</p><p>Once done, drain the <strong>farfalle</strong>, reserving a cup of the <strong>starchy pasta water</strong></p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pesto-and-pea-farfalle/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pesto-and-pea-farfalle/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>vegetable stock mix</strong> in 50ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[75ml]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [100ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pesto-and-pea-farfalle/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and 1/2 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[3/4 tsp] </span><span class=\"text-danger\">[1 tsp]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until fragrant</p><p>Once fragrant, add your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and a good grind of <strong>pepper </strong>and cook for 2 min or until the soft cheese has started to melt</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pesto-and-pea-farfalle/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once starting to melt, add the <strong>vegetable stock </strong>and cook for 1-2 min or until combined</p><p>Once combined, add your <strong>traditional Italian pesto </strong>and cook for a further 1-2 min or until creamy and starting to thicken</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pesto-and-pea-farfalle/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the sauce is cooking, grate your <strong>cheddar cheese</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pesto-and-pea-farfalle/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>drained pasta</strong>, <strong>blanched peas </strong>and a splash of<strong> starchy pasta water </strong>to the sauce and cook for a further 2-3 min, stirring constantly until fully combined – this is your <strong>creamy pesto & pea farfalle</strong></p><p>Tip: Add a splash more starchy pasta water if your sauce is looking a little dry!</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/creamy-pesto-and-pea-farfalle/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>creamy pesto & pea farfalle</strong> topped with the <strong>grated cheese</strong></p><p>Season with a good grind of <strong>black pepper</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
